description: Gets aggregated values for an asset property. For more information, see Querying aggregates in the IoT SiteWise User Guide. To identify an asset property, you must specify one of the following:

parameters.name: resolution
parameters.description: The time interval over which to aggregate data.

parameters.name: qualities
parameters.description: The quality by which to filter asset data. (string) ---

parameters.name: startDate
parameters.description: The exclusive start of the range from which to query historical data, expressed in seconds in Unix epoch time.

parameters.name: endDate
parameters.description: The inclusive end of the range from which to query historical data, expressed in seconds in Unix epoch time.

parameters.name: timeOrdering
parameters.description: The chronological sorting order of the requested information. Default: ASCENDING.

parameters.name: maxResults
parameters.description: The maximum number of results to return for each paginated request. A result set is returned in the two cases, whichever occurs first. The size of the result set is equal to 1 MB. The number of data points in the result set is equal to the value of maxResults. The maximum value of maxResults is 2500.

nested_items.name: timestamp
nested_items.description: The date the aggregating computations occurred, in Unix epoch time.

nested_items.name: quality
nested_items.description: The quality of the aggregated data.

nested_items.name: average
nested_items.description: The average (mean) value of the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: count
nested_items.description: The count of data points in the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: maximum
nested_items.description: The maximum value of the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: minimum
nested_items.description: The minimum value of the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: sum
nested_items.description: The sum of the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: standardDeviation
nested_items.description: The standard deviation of the time series over a time interval window.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: The token for the next set of results, or null if there are no additional results.
